<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEDICAL DISCIPLINARY ACTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Medical Board of California licenses physicians and other medical 
professionals. The board also investigates medical complaints and issues 
disciplinary actions. The most serious penalties include license revocation, 
suspension and probation. 
</P>
<P>
 These are the Los Angeles County medical professionals subject to serious 
disciplinary actions between Dec. 1, 1989, and Jan. 31, 1990, according to 
medical board documents. Final actions are published only after all appeals are 
exhausted. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
DOCTORS: 
</P>
<P>
Jimmy Lee Braly, M.D., Encino. Gross negligence in performing inadequate 
work-up on patient. Drug prescribing without physical examination and medical 
indication. Using fictitious name without first obtaining a fictitious name 
permit from the board. Revocation of license stayed, placed on probation for 
four years. Effective 5/24/89. 
</P>
<P>
Son Hong Do, M.D., Walnut. Conviction for filing false claims to Medi-Cal. 
Revocation of license stayed, placed on probation for five years. Effective 
12/29/89. 
</P>
<P>
Yuzef E. Gurovich, M.D., Los Angeles. Conviction for aiding and abetting an 
unlicensed person to practice medicine in respondent's office. Revocation of 
license stayed, license suspended for 30 days, placed on probation for three 
years. Effective 12/29/89. 
</P>
<P>
Eugene M. Molnar, M.D., Los Angeles. Gross negligence in cosmetic surgery. 
False insurance billing. Also, disciplined by Nevada Medical Board for false 
statement in renewal application. Revocation of license stayed, license 
suspended for 90 days, placed on probation for five years. Effective 12/29/89. 
</P>
<P>
Barry Scott Solof, M.D., Los Angeles. Gross negligence involving inadequate 
supervision of physician assistants during 1977-78. Revocation of license 
stayed, placed on probation for six months. Effective 1/20/84. 
</P>
<P>
Si Du Trang, M.D., Monterey Park. Conviction for filing false Medi-Cal claims. 
Prescribing drugs without examination and medical indication. Revocation of 
license stayed, license suspended for 30 days, placed on probation for five 
years. Effective 1/29/90. 
</P>
<P>
Marshall Stephen Tuck, M.D., Rancho Palos Verdes. Violated probation of prior 
decision by unlawfully using and possessing marijuana. License revoked. 
Effective 1/12/90. 
</P>
