<P>
Carolco, New Line in Distribution Agreement: Carolco Pictures Inc., best known 
as the company behind the "Rambo" films, agreed to have New Line Cinema Corp., 
the independent producer behind the smash "Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles," 
distribute Carolco's small-to-medium budget films. The joint venture will 
operate under the new name of Seven Arts. Carolco's big-budget films will 
continue to be distributed through Tri-Star Pictures. 
