<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: COUNCIL KEEPS ALIVE THEATER PROJECT FUNDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Funding for the Los Angeles Theatre Center was kept alive this week by the Los 
Angeles City Council, but several council members questioned the city's 
expenditure of nearly $20 million in public funds since the pioneering downtown 
theater first opened in the early 1980s. 
</P>
<P>
The council voted 9-3 to funnel $750,000 from the Community Redevelopment 
Agency to support the theater's building and operating costs. But even those 
voting in favor of the additional funds cautioned that city subsidies to the 
financially troubled theater must be reviewed. 
</P>
<P>
Many council members praised the efforts of LATC -- located near Skid Row to 
bring the arts into a troubled area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
