<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
COLLEGE BOARD TO VOTE ON CONTRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ADRIANNE GOODMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Ventura County Community College District board will vote next week on a 
contract that was ratified this week by secretaries, maintenance workers and 
other employees. 
</P>
<P>
The proposed three-year contract, ratified by a 4-to-1 margin of the Service 
Employees International Union Local 535 membership, covers more than 400 
district employees who have been working without a contract since July 1, union 
field representative Gregory Cross said. 
</P>
<P>
About half of the classified employees, who work at Moorpark, Oxnard and 
Ventura community colleges, are voting union members, Cross said. 
</P>
<P>
Under the proposed contract, employees would receive a 3% pay raise retroactive 
to July 1 and another 3% increase in January, union and district officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The district will continue to pay all health insurance premiums -- which had 
been a major issue with the employee group -- until at least July, 1991, said 
Jerry Pauley, associate vice chancellor and the district's chief negotiator. 
</P>
<P>
Then if health insurance premiums increase by less than 20%, employees will get 
a 4% raise. 
</P>
<P>
However, if increases exceed 20%, the difference will be taken from the 4% 
raise. ADRIANNE GOODMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
