<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARIE MEYERHOLTZ; PAST REPUBLICAN CLUB PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marie Meyerholtz, a longtime member of the Antelope Valley Republican Women 
Federated, has died at her Lancaster home. She was 83. 
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Meyerholtz served as president of the club in 1973 and 1974. 
</P>
<P>
Born Dec. 25, 1906, in Portales, N. M., she died Friday of cancer, said her 
daughter-in-law, Madge Hemperly. 
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Meyerholtz moved to Lancaster to 1952 and worked in the early 1960s in the 
classified and accounting departments at the Antelope Valley Press. 
</P>
<P>
She joined the nonprofit Republican women's club in the early 1960s and 
remained active until the early 1980s. On a wall at her house hung a photo of 
herself and then-Gov. Ronald Reagan taken at a cocktail party at the Century 
Plaza Hotel on Aug. 23, 1973. She often volunteered at the polls on Election 
Day, most recently in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
She is survived by her sons, H. C. (Mike) Hemperly of Lancaster and Carl 
Meyerholtz of St. Louis; a daughter, Ty Killen of Lancaster; 10 grandchildren 
and 15 great-grandchildren. 
</P>
<P>
A memorial service was held this week. Arrangements were made by Halley-Olsen 
Funeral Chapel in Lancaster. Donations can be made in Mrs. Meyerholtz's name to 
the American Cancer Society in Lancaster. 
</P>
</TEXT>
