<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST: MONTEBELLO; 
</P>
<P>
4 TRAFFIC OFFICERS TRAINED TO LOOK FOR TRUCK VIOLATORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Montebello Police Department, on the lookout for truck drivers who are 
breaking traffic laws, will soon begin special patrols of the city's industrial 
areas. 
</P>
<P>
Capt. Michael Kight said four traffic officers recently received training from 
the California Highway Patrol in order to crack down on drivers who break the 
law by driving trucks on restricted streets or are committing other traffic 
violations. 
</P>
<P>
Montebello has several large trucking firms in its industrial area on the south 
side of town, and heavy truck traffic has prompted residents to complain about 
trucks that emit too much smoke or are disrupting peace and quiet in their 
neighborhoods. 
</P>
<P>
Kight said the officers will patrol periodically. 
</P>
</TEXT>
