<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST: MONTEBELLO; 
</P>
<P>
CONCRETE REPLACEMENT FOR BURNED-OUT BRIDGE TO OPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Bluff Road bridge in Montebello, a turn-of-the century timber bridge that 
was destroyed when a firecracker ignited it in July, 1989, will be reopened 
next week after nine months of work. 
</P>
<P>
A two-lane concrete bridge with a pedestrian walkway will replace the old 
timber bridge that once crossed the Union Pacific railroad tracks beside the 
Rio Hondo south of Whittier Boulevard, said Joan Caterino, Montebello community 
relations assistant. 
</P>
<P>
Caterino said the $1.7-million project was paid for with city and federal 
funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
