<TEXT>
<P>
A finance company filed suit against Atlanta Falcon linebacker Aundray Bruce, 
claiming he failed to make payments on two mortgage loans totaling $912,000. 
</P>
<P>
American Home Funding Inc., is seeking more than $1 million. The company 
charges that Bruce, the 24-year-old former Auburn star and No. 1 pick in the 
1988 NFL draft, has not made any payments on the mortgage loans of $432,000 and 
$480,000. 
</P>
<P>
After being drafted, Bruce signed a five-year, $4.1-million contract with the 
Falcons that included a $1.6-million signing bonus. 
</P>
