<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NEIGHBORHOOD EATERY: MORE EATERIES: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAN JONES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Henry's Restaurant, 10549 Stanford Ave., Garden Grove. Opens Mondays through 
Saturdays 6 a.m. till between 10 p.m. and 2 a.m., depending on the crowd. 
</P>
<P>
Kitchen closes at 5 p.m. on weekdays and 1 p.m. on Saturdays. (714) 537-9884. A 
tightknit but friendly crowd -- off-duty cops, construction workers, bikers, 
letter carriers from the nearby post office -- gathers for breakfasts, blue 
plate special lunches, cold beers, retirement parties, you name it. Newcomers 
will feel welcome. JAN JONES 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Restaurant Review 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA071990-0171 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 249534 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
July 19, 1990, Thursday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
OC Live; Page 11; OC Live 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
60 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NEIGHBORHOOD EATERY: MORE EATERIES: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By M. FLAGG 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Villa Margarita, 103 Santa Isabel Ave., Costa Mesa. Open daily 4 p.m. to 
midnight, weekends till 2 a.m. (714) 631-6602. 
</P>
<P>
The sort of place you want to take three or four friends, scarf up some 
excellent nachos and drink some very reasonably priced and 
generous-on-the-good-stuff margaritas. The place is a dump, but a nice dump. A 
homey dump. M. FLAGG 
</P>
