<HEADLINE>
<P>
COIN TOSS DETERMINES WINNER OF ILLINOIS RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A bitterly contested GOP primary election for the Illinois Legislature that 
became a battleground in the fight over abortion was decided Wednesday by the 
toss of a coin. 
</P>
<P>
Rosemary Mulligan was declared the winner over Penny Pullen, an outspoken 
abortion foe who had held her suburban Chicago seat 14 years. Unofficial 
returns showed she lost by about a dozen votes in the primary. A court declared 
a tie after Pullen demanded a recount. Her lawyer promised an appeal of the 
coin toss decision. 
</P>
