<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: WALNUT; 
</P>
<P>
REGAL CANYON ROAD WORK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Complaining that neighborhood safety is being compromised by an absence of 
sidewalks, a group of Walnut residents have persuaded the City Council to fund 
the improvement along Regal Canyon Road south of Amar Road. 
</P>
<P>
The residents, who appeared before the council last week, cited a traffic study 
that showed that 479 vehicles pass along the road each day. They argued that 
children can't ride their bicycles along the winding road without peril and 
that pedestrians are at risk of being hit by vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
Before unanimously approving the construction of sidewalks at a maximum cost of 
$20,000, the council asked city staff to determine how many other streets lack 
sidewalks and to define the city's responsibility in installing them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
