<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ALTADENA; 
</P>
<P>
EXPLORER PROGRAM PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHP Officer Houston Currie told the Town Council on Tuesday that the department 
will launch an Explorer Program in September as a means of getting new 
recruits. 
</P>
<P>
The program is designed to train 16- to 21-year-olds, male or female, in office 
and field procedures. The 15 applicants selected will serve on a volunteer 
basis after a week at the CHP Training Academy in Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
CHP officials say they hope that the explorers will eventually sign up as 
members of the department. 
</P>
<P>
Interested residents should contact the CHP's Altadena Patrol Office. 
</P>
