<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ALTADENA; 
</P>
<P>
ENTERPRISE ZONE SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Assemblyman Pat Nolan (R-Glendale) told the Town Council on Tuesday that he is 
working to get an Enterprise Zone designation for Altadena. 
</P>
<P>
Under the Enterprise Zone concept, businesses locating within a selected area 
receive a state tax credit equal to 50% of the wages they pay employees, who 
are taken off of government financial assistance. Businesses also receive a 
sales tax rebate on equipment bought for use within the zone, plus other 
benefits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
