<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Cross-Cultural Posters: Part of a group of 20 Soviet and 50 American 
youngsters work on a design for one of two murals that will be shown in Los 
Angeles and several other cities abroad. It is part of an art exchange program 
in which students from Children's Center for Avant-Garde Art in Leningrad this 
week finished a three-week visit to the United States. The Americans went to 
Russia last year. Stephanie Tsuchida's South Pasadena studio was used to 
develop mural ideas. LOU MACK / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
