<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIRING PROGRAM FOR PASADENANS ADOPTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A "First Source Agreement," requiring developers in Pasadena to provide jobs 
for city residents first before considering non-residents, was approved Tuesday 
by the Board of Directors. 
</P>
<P>
The board also approved spending $48,756 to implement and administer the 
program. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement was devised to comply with the Growth Management Initiative 
passed by voters last year. 
</P>
<P>
The policy was initially opposed by the Pasadena Chamber of Commerce and 
Jurgensen's grocery store, which thought that it was unconstitutional and 
overly burdensome to developers and employers. They withdrew their objections 
after the policy was revised. 
</P>
</TEXT>
